  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nWhen sending a transaction that is underpriced RPC providers respond with an error whereas Nethermind client will accept the transaction without complaint\r\n\r\n**Example**\r\nThe same transaction sent to infura is returning an error:\r\n\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"error\":{\"code\":-32000,\"message\":\"transaction underpriced\"}}\r\n\r\nWhereas nethermind accepts the tx without any complaint.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nA warning or error. Controlling this response by configuration would be preferable \r\n\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nObserved in clients from v1.11.1, will update if not observed in latest version \r\n\r\n**[this issue may have some sort of relevance as well](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/issues/3577)**",
