    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Nethermind returns an error \"FeeTooLow\" only if transaction is cheaper than the cheapest transaction in full TxPool, so is too cheap to be even included in the pool. If fee is good enough to store this transaction as a pending, we are just accepting it, it has a chance to be included in block in the future, when fee drops. It's standard behaviour of nodes, Geth works the same way - for test reasons I sent transaction with 1 wei gas price to Nethermind and Geth on goerli testnet and both accepted it.",
